        <prompt>How did the "Labor Code" affect freed people in South Carolina?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Restricted worker rights and mobility</option>
            <option letter="b">Protected worker interests</option>
            <option letter="c">Increased wages</option>
            <option letter="d">Improved working conditions</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>South Carolina's Labor Code restricted worker rights and mobility by requiring annual contracts and imposing penalties for breaking them.</explanation>
